Palo Verde first appeared as a [[census-designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Palo Verde had a population of 152. The population density was {{convert|262.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Palo Verde was 108 (71.1%) [[White Americans|White]], 4 (2.6%) [[African Americans|African American]], 2 (1.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 6 (3.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 31 (20.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 33 persons (21.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Palo Verde CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0655422 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 84 households, out of which 4 (4.8%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 23 (27.4%) were married-couple households, 3 (3.6%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 25 (29.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 33 (39.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 45 households (53.6%) were one person, and 27 (32.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.81.<ref name=DP1/> There were 32 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (38.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Palo Verde CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0655422 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 5 people (3.3%) under the age of 18, 2 people (1.3%) aged 18 to 24, 15 people (9.9%) aged 25 to 44, 62 people (40.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 68 people (44.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 62.7{{nbsp}}years. There were 72 males and 80 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 153 housing units at an average density of {{convert|263.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 84 (54.9%) were occupied. Of these, 68 (81.0%) were owner-occupied, and 16 (19.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0655422|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715032312/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0655422|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Palo Verde CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Palo Verde had a population of 171. The population density was {{convert|289.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Palo Verde was 124 (73%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2 (1%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 5 (3%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1 (1%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 26 (15%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 13 (8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 33 persons (19%).

The Census reported that 171 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 84 households, out of which 11 (13%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 28 (33%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 4 (5%) had a female householder with no husband present, 7 (8%) had a male householder with no wife present. There were 7 (8%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 40 households (48%) were made up of individuals, and 17 (20%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.04. There were 39 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (46% of all households); the average family size was 2.90.

The population was spread out, with 25 people (15%) under the age of 18, 15 people (9%) aged 18 to 24, 23 people (14%) aged 25 to 44, 65 people (38.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 43 people (25%) who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 54.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 119.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 121.2 males.

There were 211 housing units at an average density of {{convert|357.3|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 84 were occupied, of which 35 (41.7%) were owner-occupied, and 49 (58.3%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 17%; the rental vacancy rate was 17%. 63 people (37% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 108 people (63%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, the median income for a household in the CDP was $12,772, and the median income for a family was $14,333. Males had a median income of $13,281 versus $9,792 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $7,275. About 45% of families and 47% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 71% of those under the age of eighteen and 13% of those 65 or over.

